Class AdditiveUnitValidator

All Implemented Interfaces:
IUnitValidator
public class AdditiveUnitValidator
extends UnitValidator

An "additive" UnitValidator; that is, one which does not do much validation. If one wants to add validations to a Unit without repeating existing validations, one can do so by extending this class. The only validations from UnitValiator that are carried forward are UnitValidator.validateCapabilityTypes(Unit, IDeployValidationContext, IDeployReporter) and UnitValidator.validateRequirementTypes(Unit, IDeployValidationContext, IDeployReporter).
